abstract: >-
  This project presents the design and development of a
  web-based conversational artificial intelligence agent
  powered by Large Language Models (LLMs). The system
  provides a text-based chat interface through which users
  can interact with the AI agent in real time. Responses
  generated by the language model are presented both as
  textual messages and through Text-to-Speech (TTS)
  synthesis, enhancing accessibility and user engagement.


  To improve the overall interaction experience, the
  platform incorporates an animated virtual avatar that
  visually represents the AI agent during conversations. The
  application also maintains a complete textual conversation
  history, allowing users to review previous interactions
  and ensuring continuity throughout the dialogue.


  The system follows a full-stack web architecture that
  integrates modern frontend technologies with backend
  services responsible for managing communication with the
  language model and speech synthesis components. The
  modular design facilitates future extensions and
  adaptation to different application scenarios, such as
  customer support, digital assistance, educational
  environments, and information services.


  This project demonstrates how Large Language Models can be
  effectively combined with web technologies, conversational
  interfaces, speech synthesis, and virtual avatars to
  create intelligent and engaging human-computer interaction
  systems.
keywords:
  - chatbot
